CHELICERAE. With 3 large widely spaced prolateral teeth (
Fig. 11D
). Without stridulating file. Three small closely spaced retrolateral denticles, positioned between the two first prolateral teeth.

PEDIPALP (
Figs 12A–D
, 
13A–F
). Patella with long strong macrosetae (
Fig. 12A
). Tibia with two retrolateral and one prolateral trichobothrium (
Fig. 12D
). Cymbium with two prolateral macrosetae (
Fig. 13A
). Paracymbium J-shaped, with unusual distal serrations on ventral margin (
Fig. 13A–F
). It holds two basal setae (
Fig. 13A
) and its distal part is well set off from the cymbium in dorsal view (
Fig. 12D
). Suprategulum narrow and triangular. Tegular mynoglenine process short and roundish (
Figs 12A
, 
13A
), smaller than in 

Afroneta serrata

sp. nov.
(
Figs 9A
, 
10A
). Radical division small restricted to distal half of alveolus (
Fig. 13F
). Radix drop-like. Embolus with broad base, robust and almost straight and tapering towards the tip (
Figs 12C
, 
13C
). Embolic membrane exceeding the embolus and the alveolus only slightly (
Fig. 13F
), less than in 

Afroneta serrata

sp. nov.
